Security Labels in Internet Email
2015", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="This document describes a header field, SIO-Label, for use in Internet email to convey the sensitivity of the message.  This header field may carry a textual representation (a display marking) and/or a structural representation (a security label) of the sensitivity of the message.  This document also describes a header field, SIO-Label-History, for recording changes in the message's label.", style=filled, fillcolor=green]; 

